-- Penguins Forward Malkin to Miss Rest of NHL Season Following Knee Surgery
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2011-02-09T21:11:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-09/penguins-forward-malkin-to-miss-rest-of-nhl-season-following-knee-surgery.html
  Pittsburgh Penguins  forward Evgeni
Malkin, the  National Hockey League ’s 2009 scoring champion, will
undergo knee surgery tomorrow and miss the remainder of the
season.  Malkin, 24, will be ready for the start of training camp in
September, Penguins General Manager Ray Shero said in a
statement on the team’s website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  